All which doe proue, not only an authority, and that infallible in the Church to direct and teach vs;The church that is, the paſtours of it. but alſo an obligation in vs to obey & ſubmit our ſelues for fayth, to the direction and inſtruction of it. And leaſt any ſhould doubt of this Church, what it is, the holy Ghoſt explicates the meaning of our Sauiour, & tells vs, that it is; 
                     Ephe. 4.11. 
                  Some Apoſtles, & ſome Prophets, and other ſome Euangelists, and other ſome Pastours and Doctours, to the conſumation of the Saints, vnto the worke of the ministery, vnto the edifying of the body of Christ, vntill we meet all into the vnity of Fayth. Which Paſtours he will giue vs, according 
